A Temporal Cloud Namespace with HA (primary: us-east-1, replica: us-west-2) is using private network connectivity via AWS PrivateLink. During a regional incident, Temporal Cloud automatically initiates a hybrid failover. The failover begins with a graceful handover attempt but the system cannot reach a consistent state within the 10-second window and escalates to a forced failover. Your application uses the Namespace endpoint `myapp.acct123.tmprl.cloud:7233` and has NOT configured any DNS refresh logic. Which of the following statements most accurately describes the post-failover connectivity behavior?

```go
// Client initialization in application
client, err := temporalclient.Dial(temporalclient.Options{
    HostPort: "myapp.acct123.tmprl.cloud:7233",
    ConnectionOptions: temporalclient.ConnectionOptions{
        TLS: tlsConfig,
    },
})
```
